<figureCitation box="[151,324,794,820]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="15.[151,250,1904,1928]" captionTargetBox="[153,1436,274,1879]" captionTargetId="figure-61@15.[151,1436,273,1881]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 4. Freyastera mortenseni (Madsen, 1956). Scale bar=3.0 mm. A. Whole body-top/lateral view. B. In situ abactinal view showing disk. C. Oral view showing mouth spines. D. Pedicellariae with articulated valves. Scale bar=20 µm E. Individual valve showing teeth on tip. F. Oral view showing tube foot groove as well as lateral and furrow spines." pageId="14" pageNumber="15">FIGURE 4A–F</figureCitation>
